Hi, I want to detect if the trough bore encoder is connected to the roborio or not directly in the code to avoid any errors caused by an unplugged through bore encoder, do you know if there is any methods in cpp to check the connection of the encoder in the dio port?
Thank you in advance
Gaspard

It’s easier to make sure it doesn’t come unplugged. There are a few techniques if detecting the fault condition is necessary, for example, see detection - Electrically detecting a not connected input - Electrical Engineering Stack Exchange
A barrel connector with a third wire “safety circuit” to detect a broken connection might be the easiest thing to do and requires another input to check for the continuity.

We ended up doing detection last year by looking at the frequency of the absolute position. Normally it’s around 975Hz, but if it gets really low we assumed that meant it wasn’t plugged in.

Ignore the isFaulted() implementation below, that should be returning whether the sensor is faulted or not (just temporarily hardcoded to False)
